
  PixEagle Commands
  ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

  Setup:
    make init              Initialize PixEagle (first-time setup)
    make download-binaries Download MAVSDK and MAVLink2REST binaries
    make binary-download-plan
                            Preview pinned binary URLs/checksums
    make setup-profile     Apply an explicit setup profile
    make qgc-video-profile Configure field QGC video (GCS_HOST=<ip>)
    make check-gstreamer-runtime
                            Verify OpenCV/GStreamer and QGC UDP prerequisites
    make managed-sih-doctor
                            Read-only managed PX4 SIH prerequisite check
    make qgc-direct-media-profile
                            Configure guarded HTTPS/WSS QGC direct media
    make demo-lan-browser-profile
                            Configure lab LAN dashboard (LAN_HOST=<this-host-ip>)
    make unsafe-demo-lan-media-profile
                            Configure anonymous lab-only media URLs
    make quick-browser-demo
                            Configure/start minimal browser demo (LAN_HOST=<ip>)
    make quick-browser-demo-cleanup
                            Stop demo and remove demo credentials with CONFIRM=1
    make production-remote-profile
                            Configure loopback backend for TLS reverse proxy
                            Use CREDENTIAL_HANDOFF_FILE=<0600-json> in automation

  Running:
    make run               Run all services (production mode)
    make dev               Run in development mode with hot-reload
    make stop              Stop all services

  Monitoring:
    make status            Show service status
    make logs              Show service logs
    make attach            Attach to tmux session

  Service Management (Linux/systemd):
    make service-install   Install pixeagle-service command
    make service-enable    Enable boot auto-start
    make service-disable   Disable boot auto-start
    make service-status    Show detailed service status
    make service-logs      Follow service logs
    make service-attach    Attach to service tmux session
    make service-uninstall Remove pixeagle-service + systemd unit

  Updates:
    make update            Fast-forward + guided dependency/config reconciliation
                            Requires the PixEagle runtime to be stopped
    Options: SYNC_REMOTE=<remote> SYNC_BRANCH=<branch>

  Maintenance:
    make clean             Clean build artifacts and caches
    make reset-config      Reset config.yaml and dashboard/.env to defaults
    make test              Run tests
    make phase0-check      Run Phase 0 guardrails
    make sitl-dry-run      Validate the PX4/SITL plan without side effects
    make sitl-probe        Probe an already running PX4/SITL stack
    make sitl-sih-dry-run  Validate the official PX4 SIH profile without side effects
    make sitl-sih-probe    Probe an already running PX4 SIH stack
    make sitl-sih-execute-px4
                            Start only the guarded PX4 SIH container and collect evidence
    make sitl-gazebo-dry-run
                            Validate the official PX4 Gazebo visual profile without side effects
    make sitl-gazebo-probe
                            Probe an already running official PX4 Gazebo visual stack
    make sitl-gazebo-execute-px4
                            Start only the guarded official PX4 Gazebo container
    make video-udp-proof-dry-run
                            Validate generated RTP/UDP receiver contract without side effects
    make video-udp-proof-execute
                            Start only a local generated RTP/UDP sender and collect video evidence
    make production-remote-browser-e2e-dry-run
                            Validate the local HTTPS/browser evidence plan
    make production-remote-browser-install
                            Install Chromium and Linux dependencies for Playwright
    make production-remote-browser-e2e
                            Build dashboard and run local self-signed HTTPS E2E
                            Requires ALLOW_LOCAL_SELF_SIGNED_TLS=1

  Windows Users:
    Use WSL for maintained setup. Native helpers are contributor-only
    experiments gated by PIXEAGLE_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_WINDOWS=1;
    review docs/WINDOWS_SETUP.md before opting in.

  ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
